title: Carjacking suspect shot, killed by Kirkland officer
text:
A carjacking suspect was shot and killed by a Kirkland police officer Thursday morning.
Police said they were called to the area of Northeast 118 th Street near the Kirkland Municipal Courthouse about 9:20 a.m. for a report of a man acting suspiciously. Officers found the man, but he was able to evade police.
A short time later, the man attempted to carjack a driver, but was unsuccessful. He then tried to steal another car, but failed, according to officers.
Then officers caught up with him again.
"There was some type of encounter with the officers. An officer fired a single shot, as far as we know at this point, striking the suspect, and the suspect was deceased at the scene," said Kirkland Police Department Sgt. Rob Saloum.
Police say the details of the encounter between the officer and the suspect are not yet clear.
Kirkland PD says suspect killed by police tried to carjack two drivers at gunpoint.
